{"title_page": "Roman Catholic Diocese of Iglesias", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=October 2016}}\n{{update|date=October 2016}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Iglesias\n| latin             = Dioecesis Ecclesiensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the native language --> \n| image             = Cattedrale Iglesias.jpg\n| image_size        =  \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = Cathedral of [[Iglesias, Sardinia|Iglesias]]\n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = {{flag|Italy}}\n| metropolitan      =  \n| territory         = \n| province          = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cagliari|Cagliari]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_km2          = 1,678 \n| population        = 145,600\n| population_as_of  = 2006\n| catholics         = 145,000<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 99.6\n| parishes          = 64<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese -->\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Catholic Church]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = 18 May 1763 ({{age|1763|5|18}} years ago)\n| cathedral         = Cattedrale di S. Chiara d\u2019Assisi\n| cocathedral       = \n| patron            = \n| priests           = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{Incumbent pope}} <!-- DO NOT CHANGE. This will update the Popes Automatically as they change -->\n| bishop_title      = Bishop\n| bishop            = [[Giovanni Paolo Zedda]]\n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = \n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = [[Tarcisio Pillolla]]\n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = \n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [http://www.diocesidiiglesias.it/iglesias/s2magazine/index1.jsp?idPagina=22833 www.diocesidiiglesias.it]\n| footnotes         = \n}}\nThe Italian Catholic '''diocese of Iglesias''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Ecclesiensis}}) is in [[Sardinia]]. It is a [[suffragan]] of the [[archdiocese of Cagliari]].<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/digle.html ''Catholic Encyclopedia'' page]</ref><ref name=CathHierIglesias>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/digle.html \"Diocese of Iglesias\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved April 24, 2017</ref><ref name=GCathIglesias>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/igle0.htm \"Diocese of Iglesias\"] ''GCatholic.org''. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved April 24, 2017</ref>\n\n==History==\n{{context|date=October 2016}}\nThe [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Sulcis|Diocese of Sulci]] was an episcopal seat as early as the seventh century. After its decline the bishop of Sulci took up his residence at the village of [[Tratalias]];<ref>[http://www.sardegne.com/sardinia-info/architecture-and-museums/churches/610-hundreds-of-churches-scattered-in-the-territory-of-sulcis-iglesiente.html Hundreds of churches scattered in the territory of Sulcis-Iglesiente \u2013 Sardinia churches \u2013 Sardegne.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> in 1503 the seat was officially moved to [[Iglesias, Sardinia|Iglesias]] but in 1514 the Diocese was reunited with the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cagliari|Archdiocese of Cagliari]]\n\nIn 1763 the see was re-established, and [[Luigi Satta]] appointed bishop. \n[[File:Tratalias cattedrale.jpg|thumb|right|Tratalias cathedral]]\nThe cathedral of Iglesias (then ''Villa di Chiesa'') was erected by the [[Pisa]]ns in 1285, but has been restored in later times.<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/07638b.htm ''Catholic Encyclopedia'' article]</ref> The previous cathedral located in Tratalias was built in a [[Pisa]]n-[[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] style between 1213 and 1282.\n\n==Bishops==\n*Luigi Satta (1763\u20131772 Died)\n*Giovanni Ignazio Gautier (1772\u20131773 Died)\n*Francesco Antonio Deplano (1775\u20131781 Died)\n*Giacinto Francesco Rolfi, [[O.E.S.A.]] (1783\u20131789 Died)\n*Giuseppe Domenico Porqueddu (1792\u20131799 Died)\n*Nicolo Navoni (1800\u20131819 Confirmed, [[Archbishop of Cagliari]])\n*Giovanni Nepomuceno Ferdiani (1819\u20131841 Died)\n*Raimondo Orr\u00f9 (1842\u2013Did Not Take Effect)\n*Giovanni Stephano Masala (1842\u2013Did Not Take Effect)\n*Giovanni Battista Montixi (1844\u20131884 Died)\n*Raimondo Ingheo-Ledda (1884\u20131907 Resigned)\n*Giuseppe Dallepiane (1911\u20131920 Died)\n*Saturnino Peri (1920\u20131929 Resigned)\n*Giovanni Pirastru (1930\u20131970 Retired)\n*Giovanni Cogoni (1970\u20131992 Retired)\n*Arrigo Miglio (1992\u20131999 Appointed, [[Bishop of Ivrea]])\n*Tarcisio Pillolla (1999\u20132007 Retired)\n*Giovanni Paolo Zedda (8 Mar 2007 \u2013 )\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Catholic}}\n\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of Cagliari}}\n\n{{coord|39.3167|N|8.5333|E|source:wikidata-and-enwiki-cat-tree_region:IT|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in Sardinia|Iglesias]]\n[[Category:Religious organizations established in 1763]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses and prelatures established in the 18th century|Davenport]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{refimprove|date=October 2016}}\n{{update|date=October 2016}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Iglesias\n| latin             = Dioecesis Ecclesiensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the native language --> \n| image             = Cattedrale Iglesias.jpg\n| image_size        =  \n| image_alt