{"title_page": "Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma\u2013Thibodaux", "text_new": "{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Houma\u2013Thibodaux\n| latin             = Dioecesis Humensis\u2013Thibodensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the native language --> \n| image             = HoumaLA2009ChurchStFrancisDeSales.jpg\n| image_size        = 250px \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = Cathedral of St. Francis de Sales\n| coat              = CoA Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux.svg\n| coat_size         = 150px \n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = United States\n| territory         = [[Terrebonne Parish, Louisiana|Terrebonne]] and [[Lafourche Parish|Lafourche]] Parishes, the eastern part of [[St. Mary Parish, Louisiana|St. Mary Parish]] including [[Morgan City, Louisiana|Morgan City]], and [[Grand Isle, Louisiana|Grand Isle]] in [[Jefferson Parish, Louisiana|Jefferson Parish]]\n| province          = [[Archdiocese of New Orleans]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_km2          = <!-- Area in square kilometers, automatically converted --> \n| population        = \n| population_as_of  = \n| catholics         = 120,691<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 58.9\n| parishes          = 39<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese -->\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = 13<!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = June 5, 1977\n| cathedral         = [[Cathedral of St. Francis de Sales (Houma, Louisiana)|Cathedral of St. Francis de Sales]] (Houma)\n| cocathedral       = [[St. Joseph Co-Cathedral (Thibodaux, Louisiana)|St. Joseph Co-Cathedral]] (Thibodaux)\n| patron            = \n| priests           = 59<!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{Incumbent pope}}\n| metro_archbishop  = [[Gregory Michael Aymond]]<br>Archbishop of New Orleans \n| bishop            = [[Shelton Fabre]]\n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = \n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = [[Sam Jacobs (bishop)|Sam Gallip Jacobs]] \n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux map.png\n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [http://www.htdiocese.org/ htdiocese.org]<!-- [http://example.com example.com] --> \n| footnotes         = \n}}\nThe '''Diocese of [[Houma, Louisiana|Houma]]\u2013[[Thibodaux, Louisiana|Thibodaux]]''' (official [[Latin]] name: '''Dioecesis Humensis\u2013Thibodensis''') is a [[Roman Catholicism in the United States|Roman Catholic]] [[diocese]] in southeastern [[Louisiana]]. It comprises [[Terrebonne Parish, Louisiana|Terrebonne]] and [[Lafourche Parish|Lafourche]] parishes, the eastern part of [[St. Mary Parish, Louisiana|St. Mary Parish]] including [[Morgan City, Louisiana|Morgan City]], and [[Grand Isle, Louisiana|Grand Isle]] in [[Jefferson Parish, Louisiana|Jefferson Parish]].\n\nBishop [[Shelton Fabre]], formerly an Auxiliary Bishop of New Orleans, is the current ordinary.\n\nAlthough a small diocese in terms of area (around 3,500 square miles), it has a large [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] population, with approximately 126,000 Catholics out of a total population of 202,000 within the parish boundaries.<ref name=diocese>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.htdiocese.org/AboutUs/tabid/54/Default.aspx|title=About Us|publisher=Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux|accessdate=2014-06-10|last=|first=}}</ref> The diocese includes part of [[Cajun]] Louisiana.\n\n==History==\nThe diocese was created by [[Pope Paul VI]] on June 5, 1977, from territory taken from the [[Archdiocese of New Orleans]].<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dhoum.html|title=Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux\n|publisher=Catholic-Hierarchy|accessdate=2014-06-10|last=|first=}}</ref><ref name=gcatholic>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/houm0.htm|title=Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux|publisher=GCatholic|accessdate=2014-06-10|last=\n|first=}}</ref>\n\n===Sex Abuse===\nIn January 2019, the Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux released the names of 14 clergy who were accused of committing acts of sex abuse,<ref>https://www.theadvocate.com/baton_rouge/news/crime_police/article_41c0fe58-15ce-11e9-97cc-67a9fcdac745.html</ref> three of whom were convicted.<ref>https://htdiocese.org/disclosure-of-names</ref>\n\n==Bishops==\nThe list of bishops of the diocese and their years of service:\n# [[Warren Louis Boudreaux]] (1977&ndash;1992) \n# [[Charles Michael Jarrell]] (1992&ndash;2002), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Lafayette in Louisiana|Bishop of Lafayette in Louisiana]]\n# [[Sam Jacobs (bishop)|Sam Jacobs]] (2003&ndash;2013)\n# [[Shelton Fabre]] (2013&ndash;present)\nOther priests of this diocese who became bishops:\n* [[Joseph Nunzio Latino]], appointed Bishop of Jackson in 2003\n* [[Oscar Azarcon Solis]], appointed auxiliary bishop of Los Angeles in 2003\n\n==High schools==\n* [[Central Catholic High School (Morgan City, Louisiana)|Central Catholic High School]], Morgan City\n* [[Edward Douglas White Catholic High School]], Thibodaux\n* [[Vandebilt Catholic High School]], Houma\n\n==See also==\n* [[Index of Catholic Church articles]]\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States]]\n* [[List of Roman Catholic archdioceses]] (by country and continent)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (alphabetical)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (structured view)]] (including archdioceses)\n\n[[File:St. Joseph Co-Cathedral - Thibodaux, Louisiana.JPG|thumb|left|300px|St. Joseph Co-Cathedral]]\n\n{{Infobox COA wide\n|image             = CoA Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux.svg\n|bannerimage       =\n|badgeimage        =\n|notes             = Arms was designed and adopted when the diocese was erected\n|year_adopted      = 1977\n|crest             =\n|torse             =\n|helm              =\n|escutcheon        =  The arms of the diocese are composed of two portions. The upper portion is composed of a red field on which is displayed a silver (white) cross that is charged in the center with a gold (yellow) enflamed heart to honor the Sacred Heart. This part also contain a blue chief (upper one-third) that contains three golden (yellow) fleur-de-lis. The lower half contains a silver (white) carpenter's square that is placed between three silver lilies. \n|supporters        =\n|compartment       =\n|motto             = \n|orders            =\n|other_elements    =\n|banner            =\n|badge             =\n|symbolism         = The arms of the diocese are composed of two portions. The upper portion is used to represent the See City of Houma and this is done by using the arms of the church of St. Francis de Sales who is the titular of the Cathedral-Church of the diocese. These arms are composed of a red field on which is displayed a silver (white) cross that is charged in the center with a gold (yellow) enflamed heart to honor the Sacred Heart. These arms also contain a blue chief (upper one-third) that contains three golden (yellow) fleur-de-lis. The lower half of the design is used to represent the Co-See City of Thibodaux by displaying the symbols of St. Joseph, patron of the Co-Cathedral. This is accomplished by using a silver (white) carpenter's square that is placed between three silver lilies, which additionally represent the French heritage of south-western Louisiana. \n|previous_versions =\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.htdiocese.org/ Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma\u2013Thibodaux Official Site]\n\n{{Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma\u2013Thibodaux|state=collapsed}}\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of New Orleans}}\n{{coord|29|35|15|N|90|42|58|W|source:plwiki|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux}}\n[[Category:Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of New Orleans|Houma-Thibodaux]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in the United States|Houma-Thibodaux]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses and prelatures established in the 20th century|Houma-Thibodaux]]\n[[Category:Christian organizations established in 1977]]\n\n\n{{US-RC-diocese-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Houma\u2013Thibodaux\n| latin             = Dioecesis Humensis\u2013Thibodensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the native language --> \n| image             = HoumaLA2009ChurchStFrancisDeSales.jpg\n| image_size        = 250px \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = Cathedral of St. Francis de Sales\n| coat              = CoA Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux.svg\n| coat_size         = 150px \n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = United States\n| territory         = [[Terrebonne Parish, Louisiana|Terrebonne]] and [[Lafourche Parish|Lafourche]] Parishes, the eastern part of [[St. Mary Parish, Louisiana|St. Mary Parish]] including [[Morgan City, Louisiana|Morgan City]], and [[Grand Isle, Louisiana|Grand Isle]] in [[Jefferson Parish, Louisiana|Jefferson Parish]]\n| province          = [[Archdiocese of New Orleans]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_km2          = <!-- Area in square kilometers, automatically converted --> \n| population        = \n| population_as_of  = \n| catholics         = 120,691<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 58.9\n| parishes          = 39<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese -->\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = 13<!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = June 5, 1977\n| cathedral         = [[Cathedral of St. Francis de Sales (Houma, Louisiana)|Cathedral of St. Francis de Sales]] (Houma)\n| cocathedral       = [[St. Joseph Co-Cathedral (Thibodaux, Louisiana)|St. Joseph Co-Cathedral]] (Thibodaux)\n| patron            = \n| priests           = 59<!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{Incumbent pope}}\n| metro_archbishop  = [[Gregory Michael Aymond]]<br>Archbishop of New Orleans \n| bishop            = [[Shelton Fabre]]\n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = \n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = [[Sam Jacobs (bishop)|Sam Gallip Jacobs]] \n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux map.png\n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [http://www.htdiocese.org/ htdiocese.org]<!-- [http://example.com example.com] --> \n| footnotes         = \n}}\nThe '''Diocese of [[Houma, Louisiana|Houma]]\u2013[[Thibodaux, Louisiana|Thibodaux]]''' (official [[Latin]] name: '''Dioecesis Humensis\u2013Thibodensis''') is a [[Roman Catholicism in the United States|Roman Catholic]] [[diocese]] in southeastern [[Louisiana]]. It comprises [[Terrebonne Parish, Louisiana|Terrebonne]] and [[Lafourche Parish|Lafourche]] parishes, the eastern part of [[St. Mary Parish, Louisiana|St. Mary Parish]] including [[Morgan City, Louisiana|Morgan City]], and [[Grand Isle, Louisiana|Grand Isle]] in [[Jefferson Parish, Louisiana|Jefferson Parish]].  \n\nBishop [[Shelton Fabre]], formerly an Auxiliary Bishop of New Orleans, is the current ordinary.\n\nAlthough a small diocese in terms of area (around 3,500 square miles), it has a large [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] population, with approximately 126,000 Catholics out of a total population of 202,000 within the parish boundaries.<ref name=diocese>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.htdiocese.org/AboutUs/tabid/54/Default.aspx|title=About Us|publisher=Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux|accessdate=2014-06-10|last=|first=}}</ref> The diocese includes part of [[Cajun]] Louisiana.\n\n==History==\nThe diocese was created by [[Pope Paul VI]] on June 5, 1977, from territory taken from the [[Archdiocese of New Orleans]].<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dhoum.html|title=Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux\n|publisher=Catholic-Hierarchy|accessdate=2014-06-10|last=|first=}}</ref><ref name=gcatholic>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/houm0.htm|title=Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux|publisher=GCatholic|accessdate=2014-06-10|last=\n|first=}}</ref>\n\n===Sex Abuse===\nIn January 2019, the Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux released the names of 14 clergy who were accused of committing acts of sex abuse,<ref>https://www.theadvocate.com/baton_rouge/news/crime_police/article_41c0fe58-15ce-11e9-97cc-67a9fcdac745.html</ref> three of whom were convicted.<ref>https://htdiocese.org/disclosure-of-names</ref>\n\n==Bishops==\nThe list of bishops of the diocese and their years of service:\n# [[Warren Louis Boudreaux]] (1977&ndash;1992) \n# [[Charles Michael Jarrell]] (1992&ndash;2002), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Lafayette in Louisiana|Bishop of Lafayette in Louisiana]]\n# [[Sam Jacobs (bishop)|Sam Jacobs]] (2003&ndash;2013)\n# [[Shelton Fabre]] (2013&ndash;present)\nOther priests of this diocese who became bishops:\n* [[Joseph Nunzio Latino]], appointed Bishop of Jackson in 2003\n* [[Oscar Azarcon Solis]], appointed auxiliary bishop of Los Angeles in 2003\n\n==High schools==\n* [[Central Catholic High School (Morgan City, Louisiana)|Central Catholic High School]], Morgan City\n* [[Edward Douglas White Catholic High School]], Thibodaux\n* [[Vandebilt Catholic High School]], Houma\n\n==See also==\n* [[Index of Catholic Church articles]]\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States]]\n* [[List of Roman Catholic archdioceses]] (by country and continent)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (alphabetical)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (structured view)]] (including archdioceses)\n\n[[File:St. Joseph Co-Cathedral - Thibodaux, Louisiana.JPG|thumb|left|300px|St. Joseph Co-Cathedral]]\n\n{{Infobox COA wide\n|image             = CoA Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux.svg\n|bannerimage       =\n|badgeimage        =\n|notes             = Arms was designed and adopted when the diocese was erected\n|year_adopted      = 1977\n|crest             =\n|torse             =\n|helm              =\n|escutcheon        =  The arms of the diocese are composed of two portions. The upper portion is composed of a red field on which is displayed a silver (white) cross that is charged in the center with a gold (yellow) enflamed heart to honor the Sacred Heart. This part also contain a blue chief (upper one-third) that contains three golden (yellow) fleur-de-lis. The lower half contains a silver (white) carpenter's square that is placed between three silver lilies. \n|supporters        =\n|compartment       =\n|motto             = \n|orders            =\n|other_elements    =\n|banner            =\n|badge             =\n|symbolism         = The arms of the diocese are composed of two portions. The upper portion is used to represent the See City of Houma and this is done by using the arms of the church of St. Francis de Sales who is the titular of the Cathedral-Church of the diocese. These arms are composed of a red field on which is displayed a silver (white) cross that is charged in the center with a gold (yellow) enflamed heart to honor the Sacred Heart. These arms also contain a blue chief (upper one-third) that contains three golden (yellow) fleur-de-lis. The lower half of the design is used to represent the Co-See City of Thibodaux by displaying the symbols of St. Joseph, patron of the Co-Cathedral. This is accomplished by using a silver (white) carpenter's square that is placed between three silver lilies, which additionally represent the French heritage of south-western Louisiana. \n|previous_versions =\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.htdiocese.org/ Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma\u2013Thibodaux Official Site]\n\n{{Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma\u2013Thibodaux|state=collapsed}}\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of New Orleans}}\n{{coord|29|35|15|N|90|42|58|W|source:plwiki|display=title}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Roman Catholic Diocese of Houma-Thibodaux}}\n[[Category:Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of New Orleans|Houma-Thibodaux]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in the United States|Houma-Thibodaux]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses and prelatures established in the 20th century|Houma-Thibodaux]]\n[[Category:Christian organizations established in 1977]]\n\n\n{{US-RC-diocese-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Houma%E2%80%93Thibodaux"}
